Watch: A never-before horizontal-bat 'helicopter shot'

timesofindia.com / Jul 25, 2024, 08:57 (IST)

It's almost a common sight to see Rashid successfully replicate MS Dhoni's 'helicopter' shot -- a rapid aerial whip from almost the off-stump towards the on-side, often resulting in a six. But in Dallas on Wednesday, Rashid added a touch of his own innovation to it.

Agniveer arrested for highway robbery in Punjab

tnn / Jul 25, 2024, 09:23 (IST)

Ishmeet Singh, an Agniveer, was arrested by Mohali police for highway robberies and vehicle thefts during his leave period. Along with his brother and a friend, they used illegal weapons for their crimes.

Bhagwat-Modi and the Hindu divided family

timesofindia.com / Jul 24, 2024, 15:13 (IST)

The RSS chief’s recent remarks, ostensibly aimed at PM Modi, have given the Opposition ammunition to point to a possible rift between BJP and RSS

CrowdStrike's explains how its update broke computers worldwide

timesofindia.com / Jul 25, 2024, 07:06 (IST)

CrowdStrike's update on July 19 caused global IT disruptions, including grounded flights and emergency service challenges. The faulty update led to system crashes, which took hours to resolve. CrowdStrike issued a memo detailing the incident and plans to enhance future safeguards.

Delhi Police may send notice to IAS officer Puja Khedkar to join probe

timesofindia.com / Jul 25, 2024, 09:31 (IST)

Delhi police intended to notify IAS probationer Puja Khedkar regarding fraud and cheating charges involving misuse of disability and OBC quotas in the UPSC exam. The Crime Branch is gathering evidence for the case. Khedkar, who was transferred and then recalled during her probation period, allegedly demanded perks beyond her rights while serving in Pune.

Placard reading 'war criminal' shown by US lawmaker during Netanyahu's speech

timesofindia.com / Jul 25, 2024, 10:03 (IST)

Democratic representative Rashida Tlaib, who is the only Palestinian-American member of Congress held up signs reading "war criminal" and "guilty of genocide", during Netanyahu's speech. She also wore a Palestinian flag pin and a keffiyeh, the black and white scarf linked with the Palestinian struggle for over half a century.
